dc_description_s: This line data layer represents bike paths for Dane County and the City of Madison, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Dane_BikePaths_2014.gdb. Other feature classes in this geodatabase include BCycle, BikeFacilities, BikeRoute, and FixedGuideWay. [Bike Paths and Trails: Generally crushed stone within rural areas; paved in urban areas. Includes most paths that can accommodate biking, but does not include all pedestrian paths.]
dc_creator_sm: City of Madison - Metropolitan Planning Organization (MPO)
